This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) subfield of Computer Science, as it focuses on the performance of a language model (M-BERT) on cross-lingual transfer tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as fine-tuning and probing experiments, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of M-BERT for code-switching and translation, which could fall under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper includes some visualizations of the model's performance, which could indicate that it also touches on Computer Vision (cs.CV) concepts.
